    {
        "id":  13,
        "user_id":  "a8312405-9f57-4c40-b94e-0ce774f93c3b",
        "key":  "messages",
        "value":  [
                      {
                          "id":  "1780921266760",
                          "tags":  [

                                   ],
                          "reply":  "Yes, several free tools. Organized by what they test:\n\n---\n\n**Performance \u0026 Core Web Vitals**\n\n- **Google PageSpeed Insights** — pagespeed.web.dev — free, no signup, gives LCP/CLS/FID scores + exact fix suggestions\n- **GTmetrix** — gtmetrix.com — waterfall chart, free tier, shows what\u0027s slow and why\n- **WebPageTest** — webpagetest.org — deep performance audit, free, shows render timeline visually\n\n---\n\n**Accessibility**\n\n- **WAVE** — wave.webaim.org — paste URL, highlights every accessibility error visually on the page itself\n- **axe DevTools** — Chrome extension, free tier — scans page in browser, lists WCAG violations with fix guidance\n- **Lighthouse** — built into Chrome DevTools (F12 → Lighthouse tab) — runs accessibility + performance + SEO + PWA audit in one click, no install needed\n\n---\n\n**SEO**\n\n- **Google Search Console** — free, official, tracks how Google sees your site\n- **Ahrefs Webmaster Tools** — free tier — site audit, broken links, missing meta tags\n- **Screaming Frog** — free up to 500 URLs — crawls like a search engine, finds every issue\n\n---\n\n**Cross-browser \u0026 Responsive**\n\n- **BrowserStack** (free trial) — real device testing\n- **Responsively App** — responsively.app — free desktop app, shows your site on 5 screen sizes simultaneously, best for responsive debugging\n- **Chrome DevTools device toolbar** — F12 → toggle device — good enough for most cases\n\n---\n\n**Security**\n\n- **Mozilla Observatory** — observatory.mozilla.org — scans headers, CSP, HTTPS config, gives A–F grade\n- **Security Headers** — securityheaders.com — checks HTTP response headers\n\n---\n\n**PWA Specific** (relevant for both your projects)\n\n- **Lighthouse** (again) — PWA audit built in, checks manifest, service worker, offline support\n- **PWA Builder** — pwabuilder.com — Microsoft\u0027s free tool, audits your PWA and generates missing assets\n\n---\n\n**Code Quality**\n\n- **ESLint** — free, local — JS linting, catches bugs before they happen\n- **Stylelint** — same but for CSS\n- **HTML Validator** — validator.w3.org — paste HTML, find syntax errors\n\n---\n\n**All-in-one starting point:**\n\nRun **Lighthouse** first (already in your browser, zero setup), then **PageSpeed Insights** for public URL scores, then **WAVE** for accessibility. Those three cover 80% of what matters and take 5 minutes total.\n\nFor your deployed game at `eswarsamanthula.github.io/pixel-blaster-dx/` — just paste the URL into PageSpeed Insights right now and it\u0027ll tell you everything broken.",
                          "title":  "Review website Links",
                          "prompt":  "Review website",
                          "platform":  "Claude",
